I was looking at the tailwind animations and noticed that you have specified keyframes for the 75% and the 100% positions of the ping animation? I believe the 100% keyframe adds no benefit here?

```
   ping: {
        '75%, 100%': {
          transform: 'scale(2)',
          opacity: '0',
        },
      },
```

If this is intentional can you explain why the CSS animation for the pulse only contains a keyframe for 50%?

```
    pulse: {
      '50%': {
        opacity: '.5',
      },
    },
```

Any answer would be great -- even if it is for my own learning :)

